******
[3] HPA Report: England & Wales
Date: Fri 28 Nov 2008
Source: HPA, Health Protection Report, Vol.2, no. 48 [abbreviated, edited]
<http://www.hpa.org.uk/hpr/archives/2008/news4808.htm#measles>


This article describes measles activity in October 2008 in England
and Wales; routine data on laboratory confirmed measles, mumps and
rubella for the 3rd quarter of 2008 are summarised in the Infection
Reports section of this issue [1].

In October 2008, 83 cases of measles were confirmed in England and
Wales, marginally higher than the previous month (72 cases) and
attributable to an increase in reports from outside London. The
number of cases in London remained similar to the number reported in
September 2008. The number of laboratory confirmed cases since the
start of the year is now 1049, exceeding the total of 990 for the
whole of last year [2007]. During October 2008, 9 percent of oral
fluid tests on notified cases of measles were positive; however, in
London, 15 percent of all samples tested were confirmed, whereas in
the rest of England and Wales, the proportion was 7 percent [The
original text contains a figure illustrating the number of laboratory
confirmed cases in England and Wales by month of onset: January 2007
to October 2008. - Mod.CP].

The North West region reported a further 11 cases linked to outbreaks
in schools in Cheshire [2]. Outbreaks in Wales, South East, East and
West Midlands reported previously are continuing [3]. The number of
confirmed cases in London remained constant for the 3rd consecutive
month, with cases reported from all 4 Health Protection Units in
London. A small outbreak was investigated in patients from the Polish
community in London.

Both D4 (MVs/Enfield/14.07 and MVs/Chester/38.08) are continuing to
circulate in different parts of England and Wales. Over 50 percent of
all confirmed cases this year [2008] have occurred in children of
nursery and primary school age [illustrated by a figure in the
original text].

References
1. Laboratory confirmed cases of measles, mumps and rubella, England
and Wales: July to September 2008. Health Protection Report [serial
online] 2008, 2(48): immunisation (Infection Reports section of this
issue).

2. Fears rise over measles outbreak. BBC Website [online] Wednesday,
29 October 2008. Available at:
<http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/manchester/7697269.stm>.

3. HPA. Confirmed measles cases in England and Wales - an update to
September Health Protection Report [serial online] 2008 [cited 7
November 2008]; 2(45): news. Available at:
<http://www.hpa.org.uk/hpr/archives/2008/news4508.htm#msls0809>.

