Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[In keeping with earlier observations, it appears as though measles
transmission continues in the UK. The newswires in the above reports,
as well as official reports posted on ProMED-mail in the past,
attribute this resurgence of measles transmission to lower
vaccination coverages ("update") in the UK related to a very vocal
(and unfortunately successful) anti-vaccination movement within the
country. One hopes that there will not be a resurgence of SSPE
(sub-acute sclerosing pan encephalitis) associated with this
resurgence of disease -- SSPE is a progressive, non-reversible
neurologic deterioration that has been linked to measles virus
infection -- a disorder that has virtually disappeared in countries
that have successfully eliminated indigenous measles virus
transmission. A pity the anti-vaccination movement has not been
presenting the true risk benefit equation of successful measles
vaccination programs so that parents are fully armed with appropriate
data for decision making. - Mod.MPP]

[A map of the counties of England and Wales can be accessed at:
<http://www.travelnotes.org/1800/UK/images/england_counties.gif>.
(Wrexhan and Flintshire are located within the region labeled Clywd
in this map).

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the United Kingdom can
be accessed at:
<http://healthmap.org/promed/en?v=54.5,-2,5>.
- Mod.CP]
